column101:
In psychological research about romantic relationships, “investments” refer to resources that are attached to a relationship which would decline in value or be lost if the relationship were to end.
Tangible investments are all the material resources that are attached to a relationship that would decline in value or be lost if the relationship were to end. Tangible investments can be physically touched. One example of a tangible investment is a house.
Please describe a tangible investment that YOUR PARTNER has invested into your relationship within the past 2 weeks. As part of your description, please describe how this investment made you feel, your thoughts on it, and any other relevant details.
column102:
In psychological research about romantic relationships, “investments” refer to resources that are attached to a relationship which would decline in value or be lost if the relationship were to end.
Intangible investments are all the resources that do not physically exist that are attached to a relationship that would decline in value or be lost if the relationship were to end. Intangible investments cannot be physically touched. One example of an intangible investment is love.
Please describe a intangible investment that YOUR PARTNER has invested into your relationship within the past 2 weeks. As part of your description, please describe how this investment made you feel, your thoughts on it, and any other relevant details.

My partner invested his time to come see me before I left for a summer job in a different state. This made me feel very happy and loved, as he had family visiting, but he took time out of his day to come see me and help me pack. It made me feel grateful that I have him in my life and it made me feel like he truly cared about me.

My partner has recently invested emotional support into our relationship. I have been going through a difficult time and I asked my partner to spend time with me while I work on bettering myself. My partner was reluctant at first, which made me feel lonely and as if I wasn't a priority. However, after a few days, my partner started to offer their time to me while I engaged in self-improvement activities. This time spent together has made me feel supported and wanted. Our conversations have been more pleasant since this event.

In the past two weeks my wife has invested a lot of time into out relationship. She (and I) have been busy trying to move and settle in a new location. That being said we have argued more and had more disagreements. Through these arguments we have learned we need to still invest time directly with each other and not in tasks FOR each other. That being said, my wife has been very conscious of the time we are doing chores and has made it clear when we are to "do nothing" and invest time in each other exclusivity. This has made both of us much happier and helped relieve stress in our lives.
We have recently got engaged and are currently planning our wedding together

I was suffering from a migraine a week or so ago and my partner had a lot of work to do, but he invested time that he really didn't have to spare on taking care of me. His time and attention made me feel loved and special. 

He always makes me feel special though, and I hope I do him as well.

column101: We bought a new mattress in the past two weeks. It was an expensive purchase, and we were thinking about it for quite some time. I'm very glad we bought it because it is so comfortable and we are sleeping really well.

column102: She has put a lot of effort into the relationship as we've been going through a really rough time. weve both been struggling greatly.
Nothing but in past we hve taken out joint loan

column101: A new carpet, - This was something we have been wanting for the past few years and if felt such a relief after we finally had it, its improved one of our rooms 10 fold
As I don’t work we don’t have a tangible investment as such, he brought a family car but it’s my name on the log book. I felt very happy and looked after and thought about when this happened

column102: She has invested her thoughtfulness. We have both started new, but separate, full-time jobs recently and from work, she will text me something sweet or if she is on break she will send me something such as a tweet that reminds her of me. it makes me feel good on the inside and puts a smile on my face. My birthday is also coming up in a few weeks and she has mentioned she has something planned that I have wanted for a long time but not even I know what it could be.

column101: My partner purchased me a iPhone last week. My current phone was broken and he replaced it for me. I felt very thankful to have him by my side.

column102: My partner invested emotional support by encouraging me to work towards and finish my PhD thesis. It helped me a lot to feel like we were working towards this goal as a team, not just me by myself. It also helped me to feel that this is a valid and worthy goal, not just a selfish one.
column177: Longterm exclusive partnership, not intending to get married

column101: Myself and my partner have been planning on having a baby for some time and as part of this we have bought a house to accomodate our family. This was a stressful and challenging time for our relationship and I feel if our relationship wasn't so strong we wouldn't have lasted. We are already very open about each others finances but buying a home together, you both have to know about everything. It could have been easy for us to blame each other when it came to being rejected for our first mortgage, my husband is a freelancer and I am on a low income, I have a small amount of credit card debt and my husband has a student overdraft. It brought us closer together, my husband earns more so he was able to save a little more but it was still our savings. When the mortgage was going to have to be solely in my name, it was still going to be our home. Luckily we were able to secure a mortgage with both of us.

column102: Feeling safe. I am pregnant and had a scare, a few actually, and my husband was there for me. Reassuring me, taking me where I needed to go and staying calm throughout.

An intangible investment that my partner has made recently in our relationship would be when she talked with me when I had a bad day. She showed me personal attention as well as spent time trying to cheer me up about a week ago. My partner is a generous person emotionally who can really turn your day around for the better. This is something I consider an "investment" into me and our relationship. If it were to end, I would lose that feeling of being so close to her. Her investment is love and laughter. It makes me feel valued rather than ignored or isolated when I am struggling with a difficult day in life. I really appreciate gestures like this from my significant other. I do not expect her to stop her entire day to cheer me up so when she tries to make me laugh, I absolutely notice it. It makes a real difference to realize someone else takes any time out of their day to recognize how you may be feeling.
My husband has surmised me with a trip awayinthe summer which made me feel very lucky and loved

I am not sure if there is anything he invested in besides his rv and football tickets over the past 2 week. I guess the football tickets would decline because if we broke up he would have no one to go with. I feel numb about the situation. I wouldn't be sad if I couldn't go to the football game. I like them but I can just as easily see them play on tv.

column101:
My partner bought a car for our son, who will be going off to college soon. It is technically ours together, since I contribute financially as well, but it is only in my partner's name, since he is the one who went to the credit union and took out the loan on a day I was unable to join him.

I suppose if our relationship ended, I would have no claim to that car, but until doing this study, I never even thought about it. I trust my partner completely, I expect our relationship to last until the end of our lives, and buying this car was a logical step in running our household with a kid who will need to get himself to school every day.
An expensive holiday

We have rented a place together and started living together just for a couple of months before I move out of town for work. This has made me feel closer to him and allowed me to understand him more. I was able to spend more time with him.

column102: Time dedicated - long distance so lots of time spent on trains travelling to visit
My partner hugged me after a close friends baby was poorly and I felt emotional about it, he made me feel safe and protected

We have recently taken out a joint loan to pay for a new car, I do sometimes get worried that if we were to seperate that I would be left paying off the rest of the loan but I also feel happy that we now have a proper family car that isn’t going to break down

column101: My partner sold his own house so we could buy our own home together as I did not want to move into his house. This demonstrated his commitment to me.

column102: We currently live together in Los Angeles (we are both from Canada) I don't have a green card so I need to go back to Canada in September. I was feeling stressed about my living situation and how expensive it is to find an apartment in Toronto for only a few months so he spoke with his parents about allowing me to move in with them. I am not sure if this is what you're looking for...but I feel like he took a risk for me and sort of took all the pressure off me. Living with his parents will add a new level to our relationship, I think it will get stronger and I will build a deeper bond with them which would make it so difficult if we ever break up.

emotional investments, he has opened up more about his fears and worries within the past two weeks as events have arisen. this has made me feel more satisfied knowing he can tell me things and i can offer advice where needed.

My partner has made an intangible investment in our relationship in the form of quality time. I am currently pregnant with his child and although he does not want to go to prenatal classes, he has made a point of coming to the weekly 2-hour classes with me (2 so far). This has made me feel like he really values our relationship, our family, and our future very highly. Despite his very busy schedule (full-time work, part-time school), he is committing to doing something that is of value to me more than to him.
There was no intangible investment, other than love.

column101: Our caravan. I feel this gives our family holidays and memories, which will be lost if we were to part.

column102: My husband puts basically every bit of himself that isn't helping him live back into me. I've been going through a hard mental state lately, and any time I need even the smallest thing to get by or feel better he has it for me, tangibly and intangibly. I will always have my doubts and he will always have his but I never truly doubt his love for me because of the way he reassures me. Little unimportant things.
My partner has listened to something I have been upset about which doesn't happen very often. This made me feel respected.

My partner and I spent some time together away. we were both much more relaxed and closer to each other. We both felt a lot happier about our relationship and the connection we had as we felt we had improved it.

column101: My partner and I recently went out to buy a new air conditioner. We had a certain brand in mind and BTU of the window unit. To our delight, we found a way more powerful model for only seventy dollars more. We got it home and it has performed wonderfully.

we have built a no dig vegetable bed together recently and have planted
various vegetables. my partner has cared for weeded and watered these vegetables

column102: My partner and myself are involved in a costume group raising money for charity, he has been talking about getting me my own costume which means he would have to spend a lot of time and money on doing this for me

My partner and I call, text, and talk a lot in real life because we love each others' minds. We have become active best friends in each others' lives, so if the relationship were to end, we'd lose an active best friend that we can talk to any time.

column101: My partner has placed a deposit down on an item that was costly. There were no real feelings there as my partner usually does this (i.e. pays for holidays etc).

column102: My partner listened to a major problem I was having in my life. I was very reluctant to talk about it but my partner made me feel comfortable enough to share private thoughts. I had doubted my current employment for some time, and the chat with my partner made me realize I should seek other employment. My partner made me feel important and special and I really appreciated what she did for me .
Leaving his home to go to rehab to work on our relationship which proves that he is committed to the relationship and wants it to work.

column101:
We recently purchased a new vehicle which she did not want at all. But was able to compromise on something we both wanted (more what I wanted than her). 

I felt a little bad about it financially, but she reassured me that if I really wanted/needed it that she was okay with it.
Paid half of our holiday together. This made me feel very secure as it is a small gesture of how we are both willing to put away time and money to spend time together.

column102: An act of love was an investment my partner put into our relationship. We hadn't been able to spend much time together so he took me out for a meal so that we could spend time as a couple

My partner has supported me through a shock family illness.  Although he works away he has called everyday 3 or 4 times a day checking I'm ok and also how the ill family member is.  He's sent supportive messages reminding me I'm strong

column101: Within the last two weeks my partner and I have bought a home together.  This gives me a positive outlook on our future. I look at the home and see us raising our family, entertaining friends, and growing old together.
My partner and I have our own homes but regularly stay at each others, we are talking about a new place together, this excites me but also scares me a little as I want to remain independent.

I don't have anything within the past 2 weeks, we bought a hoover but that's nothing major. We share our house so if anything happened then that would be affected and would have to decide who lived in it and took the goods.
We bought new wooden blinds for our home that were really expensive ...

My partner and I recently purchased a 2 person kayak together to spend some time out on the beach and lakes. This investment made me feel like we were committed to spending time together since the kayak requires 2 people to operate. We both split the cost 50/50 so I feel that we are both committed to the investment.

column102: My partner has invested his time and efforts in to our relationship in so many different ways and it makes me feel loved and appreciated.

My partner bought me a new computer for university in our study room, this made me feel happy, relieved, special and brilliant. 
He bought me the computer as my laptop had broke and i decided to design a study room for myself. I am very grateful for him and my luxurys!

column101: Within the last week, my partner has not made any tangible investments into our relationship outside of disposable goods like meals. I feel appreciated and valued when my partner pays for meals.

column102: My partner has been supportive of my new business venture. This has been reassuring and validating.

My partner recently set aside two evenings specifically to talk with me and learn more about how I'm feeling. I stay at home while my partner works, which helps reduce stress in our family life but I'm struggling in some ways and I appreciate that my partner makes time for us to delve deeper. If I were also working, I imagine that much of my need for social connection would be filled by colleagues. My partner seems to fill much of her need for social connections at her workplace. Since I stay at home, I appreciate that my partner regularly makes time for us to talk after the kids have gone to sleep. Having this time helps me relax and open up about small things that bother me but seem too mundane to discuss during the busiest parts of our days. This investment of time helps me feel loved.
My partner supported me and looked after the children when I was sick. If we were to break up I would have no one to support me and help out when I'm sick.

column101: We have arranged to have the house extended, for our growing family. This has made me feel secure, but nervous that i am now in this for ever
A pair of shoes that my partner bought for me while we were out shopping. It would lose value to me because I would not want to wear them and I would probably throw them out or sell them.

column102:
In the past week my health has not been great and my hubby has had to take on most of the household tasks including the cooking.

I came home from work the other day and the house was lovely and clean and he made me a very special meal which was delicious.  I felt very special cos he went out of his way to make sure everything was done in the house and then made me a fantastic meal that was absolutely wonderful.  Sometimes its just the little extra things he does that makes the difference especially when i'm not feeling to well.

column101: As a birthday present my partner replaced a book that was dear to me that I lost to someone else when I was young. The present made me feel very warm and listened to; I liked very much that he recalled this story that I had told him only once or twice and enough details of the book to replace it. It made me feel secure and loved.

column102: My partner has invested love towards me and our sons, this made us feel great and loving towards him. Also grateful for him, working all hours to provide for us.

Me and my partner are in a at together and have recently been Ikea in Swindon to get furniture trying to get the flat together one we done the shop together it was really nice to do together trying both to make  about flat a home we got back and built and put up all the furniture and it made us feel good the flat looked nicer and it's from our  own money from both working makes you respect it more and increases your own self esteem and moral

column101:
We have booked a holiday for October. I am very excited about it and think it'll bring more quality time together and we can pretend we are in the beginning stage of our relationship again. 

It will also mean limited time on the phone so we can talk more and not have to worry about people calling and asking questions as much. 

We have had several holidays before but this one will be two weeks long and we have booked a villa just for the two of us, so it'll feel romantic.

column102: Providing support when stressed and listening. Made me feel secure and less worried.

column101: She has come to social events with me, although she dislikes them.

Do not completely understand the question so will have to take a guess on whether this is a tangible investment. My partner proposed to me in 2016 and in the past 2 weeks we have agreed on a date and location and began wedding planning. This investment has made me feel very happy and content knowing my partners feelings for me and that we can make ourselves a proper family. I feel excited and proud that my partner wants to invest this with me and cares about me in this way.

column102: My partner is completely devote to me and our family as a whole. I had my parents visiting us and they stayed in our house for 4 weeks throughout which my partner has been very kind and loving,  made them feel comfortable and at home, he was coming early from work in order to take away the kids for a walk so that my mum and dad would have a rest. By helping them he was showing respect and love towards me as well and he always does. He is just the best husband ever. There are many other examples and I know that words are not enough to describe this
My partner has invested love into our relationship by being thoughtful and planning our next holiday together in the past 2 weeks.

column101: I had an ectopic pregnancy and it made him realise he wanted to spend the rest of his life with me and buy our first home.

A new beanbag for the lounge. Put old one was damaged and the children use it a lot so despite myself and my partner not needibg a replacement the children did. We saw one for sale whilst out shopping and we hadn't planned on getting one that day. I stated I couldn't afford to get it that particular day and would return after pay day. My partner then chose to purchase it using his own money. This made the children happy, I felt relived as it was one less financial obligation for me and I felt love toward my husband as this purchase didn't benefit him directly but our children and I like to as the affection and care he shows them.

column102: My partner minded our toddler son so that I could spend time with our 2 daughters.   I knew this was an inconvenience for him because he was tired,but I was happy he offered to do so because it helped me do something I wanted to do.
My partner looked after me when I was unwell. He cared for me and took responsibility for the children so that I could take some time to recover from sickness.

column101: My husband gave me some money from his wallet last week that I needed to pay for parking at work. I didn't have any money on me at the time, and he did. I felt grateful that he had given the money, and relieved that I didn't have to go to a cash machine on my way to work.

column102: Having a child. Made us even further cubed and support happy

column101: My partner invested in my music studio. I felt happy about it.

I have 5 children from a previous marriage and my husband is always supportive of me  and them
Recently we have had a bad time with my middle son where drugs have been involved and my husband has been my absolute rock

column102: I was recently admitted to hospital for 3 weeks. My partner visited me every single day, even though he works in London and had to come straight from the train to the hospital, so wasn't getting any time to himself and not much sleep. He did this because he loves me and I greatly appreciated that.

column101: He does a YouTube channel which would possibly fall apart if we were to break up for whatever reason. He says I'm his rock with it all. I help him with it and think of ways for him to move forward.

My partner has bought some train tickets for us to travel home tomorrow, after a holiday visiting my mum. It made me feel safe and looked after that he booked the tickets himself and took charge, knowing that doing it myself makes me anxious.

My partner bought a new mobile phone for me. Because my mobile phone's camera was not working. So we can use skype to see each other. This behavior made our relationship stronger. This investment made me feel valuable.
A second car, to benefit the family and improve family life.
My partner bought me and our daughter a dog which made us happy he is now a huge part of our family. We also own a house together which neither of us would be able to afford if we were not together.
My partner recently bought a tv smart and play 3, We both enjoyed playing video games online, I liked it a lot because it's something we enjoyed together and  I'm feeling very happy.

column102: We recently bought a bunk bed for our kids to sleep in, they used to co-sleep in our bed with us. And we downsized our bed so we can be closer at night. It has made our love connection a lot better, we haven't argued as much since all the transitions.

column101: my partner has taken on a 2nd job so that we can save to buy our first home together. this made me feel very supported

column102: I'm facing a very difficult period because I've lost my job and I'm finding a new one. Surely the fact that my partner is close to me trying to give me support when the future seems to be so dark and uncertain is a very important effort (or intangible investment) that my partner is putting into our relationship.

I HAD TO GO INTO HOSPITAL FOR A DAY PROCEDURE.I WAS WORRIED ABOUT THIS AND I EXPLAINED MY FEARS TO MY PARTNER. SHE TOLD ME SHE LOVED ME AND THAT SHE WOULD DO ALL SHE COULD TO ALLAY MY FEARS .SHE EXPLAINED IN CLEAR LOGIC HOW THE OPERATION WOULD GO AND HOW THINGS WOULD PAN OUT WITH HER EMOTIONAL AND PRACTICAL HELP.I FELT MUCH BETTER AND MY FEAR LESSENED AND I FELT LOVED SECURE CONTENT AND EMOTIONALLY SUPPORTED

column101: Discussions about getting a loan together to carry out home improvements. This made me happy that our relationship was moving forward with more committment and devolopments. This makes me feel like our relationship is progressing.

I love to sew, machine embroider, and quilt. A couple of weeks ago I had the opportunity to purchase a new top of the line sewing/embroidery machine at an excellent price. It is my dream machine. But the price was more than I could afford on my own with my resources and would need input from our and/or his resources. We discussed about buying the machine in terms of not just cost, but how much I enjoy using my machine and also how the items I make are enjoyed by both of us - quilts for beds, wallhangings in our home and other items. In the end we decided to go ahead with the purchase and resources to make the purchase were shared. The whole process reminded me of how we have shared things, worked together to make decisions and are willing to support things in our relationship that are shared but also  might be enjoyed more by one than the other. While not something that is absolutely a need, the new machine has put a smile on my face and made me recognize that he is the guy for me because of the way we work together and because of mutual respect.

column102: My partner provided me with emotional support, as I was having a very difficult time with my work responsibilities.  I was under more stress than usual and really needed to vent.  He was very patient with me, listening carefully, asking me questions, and offering any support I needed.  Talking about my situation with a partner who was really listening to me made me feel much better, as if a weight had been lifted off of me.  He gave his time and effort to make me feel better when I needed help, and it's something I would sorely miss if I were to lose him.

My partner has supported me in a change of career. He has listened to my concerns before I started the job and then listened to the "stories" I've had from said work. This made me feel happy and helped with the nagging doubts that come before starting a new job.

My partner confided in me about difficulties he is having with his mother.  She is very old and very confused and has accused my partner of 'stealing' some of her belongings.  My partner is very stressed and upset by the whole situation.  I have spent hours with him trying to give comfort, love and support.  I have also promised continued love and support.  It has made me feel good to be able to view offer this love to my partner and to see him be comforted by that.

My partner invested love, care, and support when I was going through a rough patch in my professional life. They were there for me, and supported me. 

This helped me to feel secure, hopeful and loved. It raised my mood, and allowed me to look to the future in a positive light.

last week my partner took me out for a surprise meal for my birthday.  When we go out to eat we usually decide together which restaurant we should go to, after discussing the menu, cost etc. so it is usually a joint decision.  It was unusual for him to make a decision about where we should go and actually make the booking himself.  It was a nice restaurant but a small part of me wished that I had been involved in the decision about where we should go - I would have suggested somewhere different!  However it was good of him to take it on himself to provide a surprise.

column101: We are in the process of buying a house, so in the past two weeks, my partner has brought this new place into our relationship as a tangible investment. It gives me relief knowing that he is handling so much of the details with the money and mortgage because of the anxiety that financial matters gives me. At the same time, it is exciting to think about us moving into this new home.
my partner invited me on dinner and buying a flowers
we have put money into decorating our flat  which has made me feel happy as we are making it more of a home,

column102: My partner has shown love for me during times of personal stress and this has made me feel secure and wanted .

column101: Mt partner and I bought furniture for their flat. I felt positive and provided me with some reassurance that we are progressing further in our relationship and they are committed to me.

Gave up the opportunity to go on a golf weekend to spend time with me supporting me through a difficult time due to work issues. He sat listened and gave supportive help in dealing with the situation. I did not ask him not to go on the golfing weekend he chose not to. I felt safe, supported an important.

column102:
I would say my partner has invested the intangible asset of ‘Trust’ into our relationship as you she had let me get closer to her son.

It made me feel very happy and I felt a great deal of responsibility that I have taken very seriously.

we have 5 kids 4 of them are girls the oldest is 15 years old and the youngest is 11 months old i cannot think of a specific incident as there are so many but it would never be the same or would definitely decrease the value she brings to the girls upbringing as there are to many times i would be lost without her when it comes to the girls.

column101: Our camper van needed a new battery and because I’m a SAHM I don’t have the funds to pay for it. I feel extremely lucky to have my partner and am very grateful for how generous he is.
